article.headline: Dayton 77, Akron 66
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Norman Plummer scored 19 points and Mark Jones finished with 17 to help Dayton beat Akron 77-66 for its fifth straight victory. Warren Williams also had 10 points for the Flyers (6-3), who shot 53 percent from the field and outrebounded the Zips 36-30. Darryl Peterson and Dru Joyce scored 11 points apiece for Akron (5-3), which shot 36 percent. Romeo Travis also had 10 points and nine rebounds. Plummer made 5 of 6 free throws and scored nine points in the first half to help Dayton build a 34-31 halftime lead. Akron's Cedrick Middleton hit two free throws to tie the game at 39 with 17:01 remaining but Dayton eventually pulled away from the Zips. Williams made a 3-pointer to ignite a 7-0 run that gave the Flyers a 67-52 lead with 3:55 remaining. The Flyers went 22-for-29 from the free-throw line. Jeremiah Wood also had 11 rebounds for the Zips.
